<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-10-0053 </DOCNO><TEXT>Although the majority of people in the US believe that products of geneticengineering will benefit society, they are also concerned about potentialrisks associated with deliberate environmental releases of geneticallyaltered organisms. At present, an established methodology for estimatingthese risks does not exist. However, given the current understandingof genetically altered organisms, development of a suitable risk assessmentframework seems feasible. This paper examines the critical issues associatedwith developing such a framework. 28 refs.</TEXT></DOC>